Still the Bluebird Sings
comments: The recording took place in Scheveningen near The Hague in the summer of 1941. It is stated on the label "Amerik. Refrain: Jan de Vries". At that time English music  was prohibited In the occupied Netherlands, but not American music. When the record arrived at the shops however in the December holiday season, the US had just entered the war.
